Depends: ${misc:Depends}, python3 (>= 3.8), python3-gi, python3-gi-cairo, gir1.2-gtk-4.0, gir1.2-adw-1
Description: Nepali Bikram Sambat calendar for Linux desktop
 A native GTK4 desktop calendar application that displays the Nepali
 Bikram Sambat (BS) calendar as the primary view with corresponding
 Gregorian (AD) dates shown in each grid cell.
 .
 Features include BS/AD mode toggle, public holiday highlighting,
 today accent highlight, and automatic light/dark mode via libadwaita.
 The nepali-datetime Python library is bundled inside the package.
